    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-05T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-05T20:00:00-05:00" n="739"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 840.48/24</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-06T01:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1914, 1 a.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6:45 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>283. The American relief committee request me to send the following resolution
                    adopted by them:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>Resolved that the United States Government be requested to instruct its
                        diplomatic representatives in Europe to obtain agreements of their
                        respective foreign governments to refrain from interference with any vessels
                        that a committee of American citizens may charter for the sole purpose of
                        carrying American citizens home who are detained by the derangement of
                        shipping caused by the present war; if possible, that vessels so chartered
                        may be permitted to fly the American flag.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
